<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Determining_significance">D=
etermining significance</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DSpearman%27s_rank_correlation_coefficient&amp;action=3Dedit&amp=
;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Determining significance"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>One approach to test whether an observed value of <i>=CF=81</i> is signi=
ficantly different from zero (<i>r</i> will always maintain <span class=3D"=
nowrap">=E2=88=921 =E2=89=A4 <i>r</i> =E2=89=A4 1</span>) is to calculate t=
he probability that it would be greater than or equal to the observed <i>r<=
/i>, given the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Null_hypothesis" ti=
tle=3D"Null hypothesis">null hypothesis</a>, by using a <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resampling_(statistics)#Permutation_tests" title=3D"R=
esampling (statistics)">permutation test</a>. An advantage of this approach=
 is that it automatically takes into account the number of tied data values=
 in the sample and the way they are treated in computing the rank correlati=
on.
</p><p>Another approach parallels the use of the <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Fisher_transformation" title=3D"Fisher transformation">Fishe=
r transformation</a> in the case of the Pearson product-moment correlation =
coefficient. That is, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Confidence_i=
ntervals" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Confidence intervals">confidence i=
ntervals</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypothesis_test" =
class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hypothesis test">hypothesis tests</a> relati=
ng to the population value <i>=CF=81</i> can be carried out using the Fishe=
r transformation:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e F(r)=3D{\frac {1}{2}}\ln {\frac {1+r}{1-r}}=3D\operatorname {arctanh} r.}=
">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>F</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mi>ln</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>r</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mi>r</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>arctanh</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle F(r)=3D{\frac=
 {1}{2}}\ln {\frac {1+r}{1-r}}=3D\operatorname {arctanh} r.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/a0f594863f16f787ace6ecfc2d75eb0d30f7d16a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:31.237ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle F(=
r)=3D{\frac {1}{2}}\ln {\frac {1+r}{1-r}}=3D\operatorname {arctanh} r.}"></=
span></dd></dl>
<p>If <i>F</i>(<i>r</i>) is the Fisher transformation of <i>r</i>, the samp=
le Spearman rank correlation coefficient, and <i>n</i> is the sample size, =
then
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e z=3D{\sqrt {\frac {n-3}{1.06}}}F(r)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
